Vendored libfdt
================

Source: https://github.com/dgibson/dtc
Upstream commit: f57e7df35df4a301961cbbf9433ba4e85c2ee5ed

Imported from upstream libfdt/:

- fdt.c
- fdt_ro.c
- fdt_addresses.c
- fdt_rw.c
- fdt_wip.c
- fdt_strerror.c
- fdt.h
- libfdt.h
- libfdt_env.h
- libfdt_internal.h

`fdt_rw.c` and `fdt_wip.c` are built because upstream `fdt_addresses.c`
includes `fdt_appendprop_addrrange()`, which references write-side helpers.
zuzu's DTB wrapper can still expose only read-only APIs.

The files are dual-licensed GPL-2.0-or-later OR BSD-2-Clause; zuzu uses them
under the BSD-2-Clause option.
